1
00:00:00,160 --> 00:00:02,960
more product managers and teams are getting laid off.

2
00:00:02,960 --> 00:00:08,240
The problem is the message that Daniel E from Spotify sent out with their layoffs in 2024.

3
00:00:08,240 --> 00:00:10,880
We still have too many teams doing work around the work.

4
00:00:10,880 --> 00:00:15,839
>> Even if you were told to build a thing that the execs are really excited about, you're still going to get fired eventually.

5
00:00:15,839 --> 00:00:20,880
>> If you were the CEO of this company, would you fully fund your own team?

6
00:00:20,880 --> 00:00:24,320
Frankly, most of the people I ask that question to don't know the answer right away,

7
00:00:24,320 --> 00:00:26,800
>> which is something called the low impact PM death spiral.

8
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:33,440
is the dynamic in which every medium to large company I've ever worked with finds itself in one way or another.

9
00:00:33,440 --> 00:00:39,200
It starts with adding little features here and there, making little cosmetic improvements until the next round of layoffs.

10
00:00:39,200 --> 00:00:42,320
>> You have three steps to become more of an impact first product team.

11
00:00:42,320 --> 00:00:47,680
>> So, the first is in setting team goals, no more than one step away from company goals.

12
00:00:47,680 --> 00:00:49,920
Don't let it get cascaded into oblivion.

13
00:00:49,920 --> 00:00:50,960
>> You're an ICPM.

14
00:00:50,960 --> 00:00:51,600
It's up to you.

15
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:52,239
No excuses.

16
00:00:52,239 --> 00:01:02,079
You can follow all the best practices, but if your company goes out of business, they're not going to keep writing your paycheck for 2 years because all of your OKRs were a point 6 or a 7.

17
00:01:02,079 --> 00:01:03,920
Today, my guest is Matt Lame.

18
00:01:03,920 --> 00:01:11,920
Matt is a longtime product leader, author of one of the most popular and practical books in the field of product management called Product Management in Practice.

19
00:01:11,920 --> 00:01:15,680
And over the course of his consulting practice, he's worked with hundreds of product teams,

20
00:01:15,680 --> 00:01:19,920
helping them improve how they operate and drive more impact more consistently.

21
00:01:19,920 --> 00:01:26,640
From that experience, he wrote and recently published a new book called Impact First Product Teams that I could not agree more with.

22
00:01:26,640 --> 00:01:33,200
In our conversation, Matt shares why it is so essential to align all of your work with business critical outcomes,

23
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:35,600
especially if you fear layoffs at your company.

24
00:01:35,600 --> 00:01:39,600
We talk about the low impact death spiral that many product teams fall into.

25
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:47,680
What steps an individual product team can take to align their work to business critical outcomes regardless of how their organization approaches product development.

26
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:52,799
Tips for how to push back on stupid ideas that execs ask you to build and so much more.

27
00:01:52,799 --> 00:01:57,040
The message in this episode is one that I believe every product manager needs to hear,

28
00:01:57,040 --> 00:02:00,479
especially if you don't work at a high-flying Silicon Valley tech company.

